    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - SINGLE SPEED AXLE: SPICER - REMOVE - DIFFERENTIAL</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="6">
        <title>DIFFERENTIAL</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove cotter pins and locks from bearing caps
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400706">Figure 6</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400706" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400706" filename="../figg14/G1400706.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 6. Remove Cotter Pins and Locks From Bearing Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Match mark one differential bearing cap and leg of carrier with center punch or chisel for
                correct reassembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400707">Figure 7</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400707" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400707" filename="../figg14/G1400707.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 7. Mark One Differential Bearing Cap and Leg of Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen four (4) bearing cap retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400708">Figure 8</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400708" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400708" filename="../figg14/G1400708.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 8. Loosen Bearing Cap Retaining Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <para></para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen adjusting rings, relieving bearing preload (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400709">Figure 9</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400709" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400709" filename="../figg14/G1400709.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9. Loosen Adjusting Rings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four (4) bearing cap retaining bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bearing caps (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1400710">Figure 10</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400710" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400710" filename="../figg14/G1400710.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 10. Remove Bearing Caps</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove adjusting rings.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully lift the ring gear and differential subassembly out of the carrier (Figure
                4.08).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1400711" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1400711" filename="../figg14/G1400711.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 11. Lift Ring Gear and Differential Subassembly Out of Carrier</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The ring gear side of subassembly must be tipped up for the ring gear to clear pinion roller
                        bearing retainer.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>Use care to avoid damage to the ring and pinion gears. If either is damaged, it must be
                        replaced as part of a matched set.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
